# CBC Quote Builder

CBC operates on a 25% commission model. Client pays CBC; CBC pays the chef 75%. All quotes must use
the pricing matrix below — never estimate or round. Getting a number wrong on a client-facing quote
is a serious error.

---

## Pricing Matrix

### Tier 1 — Premium Drop-Off
Client receives: chef-provided box packaging, chafing dishes or insulated trays, serving utensils,
printed menu card (CBC), dietary labels (CBC), disposable plates and napkins. CBC delivers. Client
sets up and cleans up. No on-site staff.

| Chef / Cuisine | Per-Head Price | Min Guests | Min Order |
|---|---|---|---|
| Unique Cuisine (Sushi/Japanese) | $30/head | 50 | $1,500 |
| Chinese | $22/head | 75 | $1,650 |
| Mexican Fusion | $26/head | 100 | $2,600 |

### Tier 2 — Attended Service
Everything in Tier 1 plus 1–2 on-site CBC staff for setup, buffet maintenance, and cleanup.
Proper linen and labeled stations.

| Chef / Cuisine | Per-Head Price | Min Guests | Min Order |
|---|---|---|---|
| Unique Cuisine (Sushi/Japanese) | $48/head | 100 | $4,800 |
| Chinese | $38/head | 75 | $2,850 |
| Mexican Fusion | $44/head | 100 | $4,400 |

### Coming Soon (pricing TBD)
- Cold-pressed juice
- Tacos
- Thai food

---

## Commission Math

For every order:

```
Client pays:    [per-head price] × [guest count] = Gross Revenue
Chef receives:  Gross Revenue × 0.75
CBC retains:    Gross Revenue × 0.25
```

Example: Sushi, Tier 1, 80 guests
- Gross: $30 × 80 = $2,400
- Chef: $2,400 × 0.75 = $1,800
- CBC: $2,400 × 0.25 = $600

---

## Additional Costs (CBC-side)

### Tier 1 — CBC Service Kit
~$50–$100 per order: dietary labels, printed menu cards, dietary breakdown sheets, delivery
fuel/vehicle. Packaging is the chef's cost.

### Tier 2 — Staff Costs
- Staff loaded cost: $30/hr (includes taxes + workers comp)
- Billed to client: $35–$45/hr
- Typical event: 2 staff × 4 hours = $240 cost, $280–$360 billed
- Staff contribution per event: $40–$120 above labor cost (on top of commission)

---

## Quote Document Structure

When generating a quote, include all of the following:

```
CULINARY BLOCK COLLECTIVE — CATERING QUOTE

Prepared for: [Client Name], [Company]
Date: [Today]
Event Date: [Requested date]
Valid Until: [Today + 14 days]

─────────────────────────────────────────

MENU: [Cuisine] by [Chef Name]
SERVICE TIER: [Tier 1 — Premium Drop-Off / Tier 2 — Attended Service]

Guests: [N]
Per-head rate: $[X]
                                    ─────────
Subtotal:                          $[amount]

[If Tier 2:]
On-site staff (2 staff × 4 hrs @ $[rate]/hr):  $[amount]

                                    ─────────
TOTAL:                             $[total]

─────────────────────────────────────────

WHAT'S INCLUDED:
• [List items based on tier — see tier descriptions above]

DIETARY ACCOMMODATIONS:
• CBC provides printed dietary labels for all items
• Please share any dietary restrictions at least 5 business days before the event

MINIMUM ORDER: [N] guests / $[amount]

PAYMENT TERMS: Invoice sent after event. Net 15.

CANCELLATION POLICY:
• 5+ business days: [TBD — see docs/operations.md]
• Under 5 business days: [TBD — see docs/operations.md]

─────────────────────────────────────────

Questions? Contact Doug at [phone/email]
```

Save quote documents to `CBC_Sales/04_Quotes/`.

---

## Validation Rules

Before outputting any quote, verify:

1. Guest count meets the minimum for the selected cuisine and tier
2. Total equals per-head rate × guest count (plus staff if Tier 2)
3. Commission split is exactly 25/75 if showing internal numbers
4. Per-head rate matches the pricing matrix exactly — no rounding, no custom pricing
5. Valid-until date is 14 days from quote date
6. If guest count is below minimum, say so and show what the minimum order would be

---

## Multi-Cuisine Orders

For events requesting more than one cuisine:
- Quote each cuisine line separately
- Each cuisine has its own minimum (applied independently)
- Staff costs for Tier 2 are shared (don't double the staff line)
- Total = sum of all cuisine subtotals + one staff line if Tier 2

---

## Internal vs Client-Facing

- **Client-facing quotes** show: per-head rate, guest count, subtotal, staff (if Tier 2), total,
  inclusions, terms. Never show commission split or chef payout.
- **Internal summaries** show: everything above plus chef payout (75%), CBC commission (25%),
  CBC service kit cost, net CBC margin.

When asked to "quote" or "proposal" without qualification, default to client-facing. Only show
internal breakdown when explicitly asked or when the context is clearly operational/planning.
